Anthony A. Ibarguen  President, Director and Chief Executive Officer of Quench, AquaVenture Holdings LimitedAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships58$6,101,217As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Anthony A. Ibarguen, also known as Tony, serves as the Chief Executive Officer at Quench USA, Inc. Currently, Mr. Ibarguen has been the Chief Executive Officer at Quench USA Holdings LLC since October 2010. He serves as President of AquaVenture Holdings Limited (formerly, AquaVenture Holdings LLC) since June 2014. Mr. Ibarguen serves as an Advisor at Knight Foundation. Mr. Ibarguen has over 25 years of experience in the technology industry. He has made and managed ... investments in over a dozen early and growth stage software, internet and IT services companies. He served as an Interim President and Interim Chief Executive Officer at Insight Enterprises, Inc. from September 2009 to December 2009. He served as the Chief Executive Officer, President and Chairman of Alliance Global Services LLC. From 2004 to 2008, he served as the Chief Executive Officer of Alliance Consulting Group. Mr. Ibarguen served as the Managing Director of Business and IT Services at Safeguard Scientifics, Inc. since January 2002. He served as the President of Professional Services, Managing Director and Venture Partner at Internet Capital Group from December 1999 to October 2001. Prior to that, he served as the Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of Ajunto, Inc. from July 2001 to October 2001. Mr. Ibarguen served as the President of the Americas and Chief Operating Officer at Tech Data Corporation from September 1996 to 2000. Prior to that, he served as a Co-Founder and Executive Vice President of Sales and Marketing at Entex Information Services Inc. from August 1993 to August 1996. Prior to that, Mr. Ibarguen worked at IBM, where he held Sales, Marketing and Management positions. He has been a Director AquaVenture Holdings Limited since June 2014. He serves as a Presiding Director of Insight Enterprises, Inc. and has been its Independent Director since July 2008. He serves as a Member of Advisory Board of Seven Springs Partners, LLC. He serves as a Director of Codi. He has been a Director of SMDK Corp. since August 1999. Previously, Mr. Ibarguen served as the Chairman and Director of Alliance Life Sciences Consulting Group Inc. and on Board of Trustees of The Baldwin School and the Pennsylvania Academy of Fine Arts. He served as Independent Director of C-COR, Inc. from October 14, 2003 to December 2007. He served as a Director of Mantas, Inc.; Fortress Technologies, Inc.; Kanbay International; eMerge; eCredit; Metalsite; and USGift. From 1996 to 2000, he served as a director of Tech Data Corp. Mr. Ibarguen received an M.B.A. from the Harvard Business School and a B.A. in Marketing from the Boston College. 2008.Read Full Background




